verses.roman:
śrī-rūpa-sanātana rahe rāmakeli-grāme
prabhure miliyā gelā āpana-bhavane

synonyms: śrī-rūpa-sanātana—the brothers named Rūpa and Sanātana; rahe—stayed; rāmakeli-grāme—in Rāmakeli; prabhure—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; miliyā—meeting; gelā—went back; āpana-bhavane—to their own homes.
translation: After meeting Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu in the village of Rāmakeli, the brothers Rūpa and Sanātana returned to their homes.
